  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Straton, of Sardeis, Epigrammatist, lived between the 1st cent.
    BC and the 2nd cent. AD [2]. Author of a collection of paederotic verse (satirically only Anth. Pal.
    11,117, for which his authorship is disputed, but cf. [5]). Some 100 poems survive, almost all in Anth. 
    Pal. 12 (1-4 presumably the beginning of the collection, 258 the coda). The topical motifs 
    are embellished with often quite scurrilous features...." Albiani, Maria Grazia (Bologna). 
    "Straton." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and
    Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2011. Brill Online.</mads:note>
